79
00:04:57,444 --> 00:04:59,356
<font color=#FFFF5E>Very clever, Mr. Lawson.</font>

80
00:04:59,557 --> 00:05:02,498
<font color=#FFFF5E>Yes, Dutch Boy was
an international effort.</font>

81
00:05:02,602 --> 00:05:06,185
<font color=#FFFF5E>And yes, it may one day,
very well belong to the world.</font>

82
00:05:06,386 --> 00:05:09,483
<font color=#FFFF5E>But until it does, we have
authority over its operation.</font>

83
00:05:09,685 --> 00:05:12,078
<font color=#FFFF5E>And we have authority over you.</font>

84
00:05:12,179 --> 00:05:14,470
<font color=#FFFF5E>And you have been
flouting that authority.</font>

85
00:05:14,671 --> 00:05:17,293
<font color=#FFFF5E>I-I have report after report here.</font>

86
00:05:17,394 --> 00:05:19,778
<font color=#FFFF5E>"Failure to follow procedures".</font>

87
00:05:19,879 --> 00:05:22,122
<font color=#FFFF5E>Numerous violations
of the chain of command.</font>

88
00:05:22,423 --> 00:05:25,950
<font color=#FFFF5E>And then, there was the
incident where you punched</font>

89
00:05:26,054 --> 00:05:28,291
<font color=#FFFF5E>a federal inspector in the face.</font>

90
00:05:28,492 --> 00:05:30,381
<font color=#FFFF5E>Well, your federal inspector
doesn't know</font>

91
00:05:30,582 --> 00:05:33,288
<font color=#FFFF5E>that a capacitor holds a charge
even when it's disconnected.</font>

92
00:05:33,489 --> 00:05:36,220
<font color=#FFFF5E>He was grabbing for the damn thing.
I saved his life.</font>

93
00:05:36,421 --> 00:05:39,766
<font color=#FFFF5E>You can make all the
excuses you want, Mr. Lawson.</font>

94
00:05:39,967 --> 00:05:42,356
<font color=#FFFF5E>But there's one thing
you cannot defend.</font>

95
00:05:42,557 --> 00:05:46,090
<font color=#FFFF5E>And that would be the day
you brought Dutch Boy online</font>

96
00:05:46,208 --> 00:05:48,786
<font color=#FFFF5E>and operational without our consent.</font>

97
00:05:48,987 --> 00:05:50,547
<font color=#FFFF5E>And what would that
have taken, Senator?</font>

98
00:05:50,723 --> 00:05:53,176
<font color=#FFFF5E>There were a series
of storms building</font>

99
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:54,874
<font color=#FFFF5E>in Southeast Asia
and the North Atlantic</font>

100
00:05:54,975 --> 00:05:57,726
<font color=#FFFF5E>that would have killed
tens of thousands of people.</font>

101
00:05:58,227 --> 00:06:00,560
<font color=#FFFF5E>Dutch Boy was ready.
We went green.</font>

102
00:06:00,664 --> 00:06:02,145
<font color=#FFFF5E>It works. You're welcome.</font>

103
00:06:02,347 --> 00:06:05,898
<font color=#FFFF5E>Mr. Lawson, if you continue
to defy our authority,</font>

104
00:06:05,924 --> 00:06:08,867
<font color=#FFFF5E>Dutch Boy will go on
without you!</font>

105
00:06:09,569 --> 00:06:12,571
<font color=#FFFF5E>Am I making myself clear?</font>

106
00:06:19,568 --> 00:06:20,568
<font color=#FFFF5E>Yes.</font>

107
00:06:20,965 --> 00:06:23,645
<font color=#FFFF5E>Good.
Oh, and one more thing.</font>

108
00:06:23,847 --> 00:06:25,422
<font color=#FFFF5E>To ensure compliance,</font>

109
00:06:25,526 --> 00:06:27,998
<font color=#FFFF5E>this committee will be sending up
new support staff.</font>

110
00:06:28,398 --> 00:06:30,062
<font color=#FFFF5E>Naturally, when they get up there,</font>

111
00:06:30,166 --> 00:06:32,403
<font color=#FFFF5E>you'll have to send some of
your people home.</font>

112
00:06:33,304 --> 00:06:34,802
<font color=#FFFF5E>We'll leave those choices up to you.</font>

113
00:06:35,004 --> 00:06:36,477
<font color=#FFFF5E>Senator, respectfully,</font>

114
00:06:36,681 --> 00:06:39,056
<font color=#FFFF5E>my crew didn't do
anything wrong.</font>

115
00:06:39,257 --> 00:06:41,392
<font color=#FFFF5E>Excuse me,
I'm not asking for your input.</font>

116
00:06:41,592 --> 00:06:43,877
<font color=#FFFF5E>These people left their homes,</font>

117
00:06:43,978 --> 00:06:45,941
<font color=#FFFF5E>and their families,
and risked their lives...</font>

118
00:06:46,042 --> 00:06:47,853
<font color=#FFFF5E>- to save this planet.
- This hearing is adjourned.</font>

119
00:06:47,854 --> 00:06:49,854
<font color=#FFFF5E>I'm not cutting a single one
of those people loose!</font>

120
00:06:49,935 --> 00:06:50,936
<font color=#FFFF5E>Excuse me?</font>

121
00:06:51,137 --> 00:06:53,875
<font color=#FFFF5E>People like you need people
like me. You know why?</font>

122
00:06:53,975 --> 00:06:56,574
<font color=#FFFF5E>So you can take credit
for everything we accomplish.</font>

123
00:06:56,775 --> 00:06:58,754
<font color=#FFFF5E>So you can go to your constituents</font>

124
00:06:58,855 --> 00:07:00,256
<font color=#FFFF5E>- and your cronies.
- This meeting is adjourned.</font>

125
00:07:00,257 --> 00:07:03,034
<font color=#FFFF5E>And your mistresses.
And pump out your chest</font>

126
00:07:03,235 --> 00:07:05,123
<font color=#FFFF5E>- and say, "Hey, look at me!"
- Sit down, please!</font>

127
00:07:05,124 --> 00:07:06,764
<font color=#FFFF5E>- Well, I'm looking, Senator.
- Excuse me.</font>

128
00:07:06,913 --> 00:07:08,661
<font color=#FFFF5E>- We're all looking.
- This meeting is adjourned.</font>

129
00:07:08,662 --> 00:07:11,489
<font color=#FFFF5E>This meeting is adjourned!
Thank you.</font>

130
00:07:17,628 --> 00:07:19,758
<font color=#FFFF5E>That was going well, huh?</font>

